      "data": {
        "title": "Produces outer fragment context plus inner ring-by-ring representation",
        "body": "Output is a representation ladder keyed to fragment selection, node distance, and load state. The outer bullseye identifies the selected fragment context. Inside that fragment, the center of the inner bullseye renders the focused node under direct user attention and is the only ring allowed to use full graph render. The graph root remains rendered at node-view regardless of selection state. The second ring renders directly connected children through an exposed child-facing surface when one exists, otherwise through their node-view. The second ring is not allowed to collapse to icon-view. The third ring renders nodes one connection farther out as icon-view when loaded or as type badge when not yet loaded. The fourth ring renders nodes one more connection out as dots. Loader work proceeds outward by ring inside the selected fragment. Cached data may satisfy a ring immediately, but only within that ring's representation cap. If a runtime-generated root is active, discovered sibling `.node` files are exposed as second-ring children using port-view first and icon-view fallback.",
