      "data": {
        "title": "Outer Bullseye Selects Fragment, Inner Bullseye Resolves Node Distance",
        "body": "Do not collapse all semantic zoom into one heuristic. The outer bullseye selects fragment context. The inner bullseye describes node distance inside that selected fragment, while rendering at a ring still depends on what has already been loaded. The center is full graph render under direct user attention. The graph root always remains at node-view regardless of selection state. The second ring renders an exposed child-facing surface when one exists and otherwise renders node-view. The second ring never collapses to icon-view. The third ring is icon-view when loaded or type badge when not yet loaded. The fourth ring is dot. Fragment selection changes recompute the outer context. Node focus changes recompute the inner rings. Cache may satisfy the new target band immediately without exceeding its cap.",
        "severity": "high",
